The paper discusses the challenges of managing and scheduling resources in a distributed system, which falls under the category of Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC). The paper also mentions the use of middleware services, which is a common topic in Distributed Systems (cs.Distributed Systems). The focus on developing scheduling schemes and computational economy suggests a connection to Software Engineering (cs.SE) and Computational Economics (cs.CE). Finally, the use of a modular and component-based architecture suggests a connection to Programming Languages (cs.PL).
